##DESCRIPTION
##  Find the total and mean of a set of bank deposits.
##ENDDESCRIPTION

## ProblemTester('Laura Travis')
## Publisher('Prentice Hall')
## DBsubject(Statistics)
## DBchapter(Exploratory data analysis/descriptive statistics)
## DBsection(Summary statistics)
## Date(9/1/2012)
## Institution(Mississippi College)
## Author(John Travis)
## Level(2)
## MO(1)
## TitleText1('Pre-Algebra')
## KEYWORDS('prealgebra','common core')

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGstatisticsmacros.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

Context('LimitedNumeric');

@data = map { random(10, 200, 5) } (1 .. 5);

($sum) = stats_SX_SXX(@data);

BEGIN_PGML

The following deposits were made into a bank account last month:
[@ join(', ', map { "\$$_"} @data) @]

a) The total of all deposits = $[_]{Real($sum)}{10}

b) The average amount of the deposits = $[_]{Real($sum/5)}{10}
END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a) The total of the deposits is the sum or $[$sum].

b) The average of the depositis is [`` \frac{[$sum]}{5} = $[@ $sum/5 @] ``]
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();   